**Fetch API**
Fetch API is a set of built-in functions and tools that we can use when we are writing JavaScript code in order to make HTTP requests.

const response = await fetch(url, settings);
const responseData = await response.json();

## Full Example

async function getUsers() {  
  const response = await fetch("https://api.example.com/users");  
  
  if (!response.ok) {  
    throw new Error("Request failed");  
  }  
  
  const data = await response.json();  
  console.log(data);  
}

---

## 🔹 Key Takeaways

- `fetch()` → sends request
- `response` → metadata + raw body
- `.json()` → converts response into usable data
- Always use `await` twice
